The paper discusses synchronization in networks of oscillating nodes, which is a topic commonly studied in the fields of systems and control (cs.SY), network science (cs.NE), and machine learning (cs.LG). The specific application domains mentioned in the abstract (power systems and neuronal networks) suggest that the paper may also fall under the subcategories of signal processing (cs.SI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the use of submodular optimization techniques is a common tool in discrete mathematics (cs.DM), which further supports the inclusion of this subcategory.
